The Jaguar's Children: Pre-Classic Central Mexico
Museum of Primitive Art | 1965 | Eng | 134 pages | PDF | 11 MB

The Jaguar's Children: Pre-Classic Central Mexico has as its subject one of the most arresting topics of New World prehistory. The Olmec of Mexicoâ€”originators of the earliest great civilization in Middle America produced an extraordinary art. Its impact on contemporary and subsequent Mexican developments was enormous. It is this impact on an area in the Central Highlands, parts of the states of Morelos, Puebia, and the Valley of Mexico, that is described here by Michael D. Coe of Yale University
